Content: Hiya everyone! I had a quick question that I was hoping KMD developers could answer. Do all Komodo based projects (Hush, Pearl-Pay, Chainzilla, Pirate etc) support atomic swaps by default?

Author: Wolf of RES#8148
Content:
Thanks for answering promptly @0x03  , reason for my question is as follows! 

I am involved with Resistance.io team , which is launching ResDEX decentralized exchange in coming months.. Short tldr;  ResDEX uses instant atomic swaps (within 30 sec trades) for decentralized trading (using RES as collateral) and zk-Snarks for Privacy.

Author: Wolf of RES#8148
Content: TOR routing is supported natively as well on ResDEX.  RES coin itself is CPU mineable (rewards split between Proof of Research, Proof of Work)  and anyone can check out working prototype through https://respool.io

Author: Wolf of RES#8148
Content:
@Cryptoon  and @crumb  that is because ResDEX uses RES as collateral on exchange (locked during duration of trade) By locking RES as collateral, you can trade funds by skipping the block confirmations. 

So basically two types of swaps are possible: 
1) Simple one where you don't lock RES as collataral and that is dependent on independent blockchain confirmation times.
2) Instant where you lock RES and that happens in around 30 sec.

Author: Wolf of RES#8148
Content:
Resistance DEX has option for non-private & private-trade. For private trade, RES gets used as intermediary token (thereby providing the necessary privacy using snarks) ; else you can do normal swap.

For non private trades, RES doesn't get used as intermediary. Again similar to how @KomodoWorld  describes Barterdex.

Content: as for your question barterdex traffic is very low, there's an easier to use gui called hyperdex but, speaking as user, the hard part is matching utxo, strange errors and unstable connections. People skilled with cli have no problems though. All these issues should be fixed in v2 that is currently in testing. With v2 uxto will always match and uses the dht protocol of bittorrent, it will be easier for home users to provide liquidity
